crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The analyzed binary is a sophisticated Trojan/Infostealer. It employs extensive obfuscation and anti-analysis techniques, including the dynamic resolution of nearly all Windows APIs at runtime to evade static detection. Key malicious behaviors include: 1) Evasion: A locale-check routine (sub_404819) that targets or avoids specific CIS languages (e.g., Russian 0x419, Ukrainian 0x422). 2) Spyware: Screen capture functionality (sub_404255) that generates BMP files of the desktop and manages them via the Registry. 3) Exfiltration: A custom Base64 encoding implementation (sub_403529) paired with WinInet-based HTTP POST routines (sub_4031ee) for data exfiltration to a C2 server. 4) Process Masquerading: Manipulation of the Process Environment Block (PEB) (sub_40380c) to overwrite the ImagePathName and CommandLine, hiding the process's true identity from system monitoring tools.
